        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 5:13PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 513 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Roosevelt, moving southwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roosevelt and I-10 Near The Sutton-Kimble County Line.

This includes Interstate 10 between Mile Markers 420 and 445.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
